"a.狡猾的 【英】 adj.狡猾的 (full of wiles；crafty) 【例】 a wily fraud(狡猾的骗子) adj. 老谋深算的; 诡计多端的 【记】读: 歪理, 总是给人家讲歪理－诡计多端的源于: wile(n /v 诡计; 欺骗) 【记】wile + y，音：歪 wily (adj.)  ""subtle, cunning, crafty,"" early 14c., from wile (n.) + -ly (1). Related: Wiliness. In 16c. English had wily-pie ""cunning fellow."""
